  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX spot at 6829.88 sitting just below the massive +119.4B gamma wall at 6830, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher as they hedge their long gamma exposure. The thick cluster of positive gamma from 6820-6850 creates a strong magnet effect that should cap upside momentum and pull price back toward this zone on any weakness. Key levels to watch are the 6830 max gamma strike as immediate resistance and the 6747 flip point below, where dealer behavior would shift from stabilizing to amplifying moves.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned near 6830 with limited upside as dealers sell strength.",
